SIMPLE: please
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Please
<hw>Please</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Pleased</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Pleasing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>plesen</ets>, OF.
<ets>plaisir</ets>, fr. L. <ets>placere</ets>, akin to
<ets>placare</ets> to reconcile. Cf. <er>Complacent</er>,
<er>Placable</er>, <er>Placid</er>, <er>Plea</er>, <er>Plead</er>,
<er>Pleasure</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To give pleasure to; to
excite agreeable sensations or emotions in; to make glad; to gratify; to
content; to satisfy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I pray to God that it may <qex>plesen</qex> you.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What next I bring shall <qex>please</qex> thee, be assured.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To have or take pleasure in; hence, to choose; to
wish; to desire; to will.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whatsoever the Lord <qex>pleased</qex>, that did he.</q>
<rj><qau>Ps. cxxxv. 6.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A man doing as he wills, and doing as he <qex>pleases</qex>, are
the same things in common speech.</q> <rj><qau>J.
Edwards.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To be the will or pleasure of; to seem good to; --
used impersonally.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧It <xex>pleased</xex> the Father that in
him should all fullness dwell.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Col. i. 19.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To-morrow, may it <qex>please</qex> you.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>To be pleased in</b></col> <it>or</it> <col><b>To
be pleased with</b></col></mcol>, <cd>to have complacency in; to take
pleasure in.</cd> -- <col><b>To be pleased to do a thing</b></col>,
<cd>to take pleasure in doing it; to have the will to do it; to think
proper to do it.</cd> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Please</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Please
<hw>Please</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
afford or impart pleasure; to excite agreeable emotions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What <qex>pleasing</qex> scemed, for her now <qex>pleases</qex>
more.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For we that live to <qex>please</qex>, must <qex>please</qex> to
live.</q> <rj><qau>Johnson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To have pleasure; to be willing, as a matter of
affording pleasure or showing favor; to vouchsafe; to consent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Heavenly stranger, <qex>please</qex> to taste⟦br⟧
These bounties.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That he would <qex>please</qex> 8give me my liberty.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pleased</ent>⟦br⟧
